WEBVTT

00:01.610 --> 00:02.645
Charley:
Previously on
"Queen Sugar"...

00:02.690 --> 00:04.169
Ralph Angel:
It's Blue.

00:04.220 --> 00:07.041
She said he ain't mine,
that he ain't my son.

00:07.090 --> 00:08.523
Darla:
I just couldn't go through
with the wedding

00:08.570 --> 00:09.958
without him
knowing everything.

00:10.010 --> 00:11.170
That wouldn't
have been right.

00:11.220 --> 00:12.528
Ain't none of it right.

00:12.570 --> 00:15.482
I have never known
a woman like you before.

00:15.530 --> 00:17.964
Someone's out here pitching
a story about all the internal
issues at Queen Sugar.

00:18.010 --> 00:19.659
But there_ are
no Internal Issues.

00:19.710 --> 00:22.270
- I need to trust you.
- And you can.

00:22.320 --> 00:23.833
Don't let them white boys
get in your head.

00:23.890 --> 00:25.539
Stand up to them.

00:25.590 --> 00:26.978
You can turn it around.

00:27.020 --> 00:28.885
Fight back.

00:28.940 --> 00:30.714
Yeah, I'll fight,
all right.

00:35.030 --> 00:38.158
I can tell you
what it is,

00:38.210 --> 00:40.201
but I have to use
a bad word.

00:42.040 --> 00:46.602
I heard someone say,
"That damn girl."

00:46.650 --> 00:49.380
I think they were
talking about Mommy.

00:51.000 --> 00:52.046
[ sighs ]

00:55.530 --> 00:56.781
Violet:
Hey, Blue.

00:56.830 --> 00:58.525
Hey, Aunt Vi.

00:58.580 --> 01:01.140
- Want some company?
- Sure.

01:02.410 --> 01:04.184
What you doing?

01:04.230 --> 01:07.313
Putting one of those
into a little pot.

01:10.070 --> 01:12.630
[ humming ]

01:22.120 --> 01:24.031
I remember that song.

01:24.080 --> 01:26.253
You do?

01:26.300 --> 01:29.167
This little light
of mine

01:29.210 --> 01:31.644
I'm gonna let it shine

01:31.700 --> 01:35.170
Ooh, this little light
of mine

01:35.220 --> 01:38.132
I'm gonna let it shine

01:38.180 --> 01:40.694
This little light
of mine

01:40.750 --> 01:42.911
I'm gonna
let it shine

01:42.970 --> 01:47.748
Let it shine,
let it shine,
let it shine.

01:49.230 --> 01:51.016
Mmm.

01:54.810 --> 01:57.062
You like it?

01:57.110 --> 01:59.897
I love it.

01:59.940 --> 02:02.636
I love it, love it,
love it, love it, love it.

02:02.680 --> 02:05.410
[ music playing ]

02:05.470 --> 02:09.645
Dreams never die,
take flight, as the
world turns

02:09.690 --> 02:12.989
Dreams never die,
take flight, as the world
turns

02:13.040 --> 02:15.429
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight

02:17.480 --> 02:19.345
Dreams never die

02:24.790 --> 02:28.874
Keep the colors
in the lines

02:28.930 --> 02:32.661
Keep the colors
in the lines, take flight.

02:32.710 --> 02:34.234
If you could give me
your full name, sir?

02:34.280 --> 02:35.793
Elijah Macon.

02:35.850 --> 02:38.808
I'm a second generation
sugarcane farmer.

02:38.850 --> 02:41.978
Are you aware of any breakdowns
or equipment malfunctions
at the Queen Sugar Mill?

02:42.030 --> 02:43.895
No, ma'am.

02:43.940 --> 02:46.852
Can you share a little
about your experience?

02:46.900 --> 02:49.721
Feel free to keep it simple.
Just tell the truth.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.203
I'd be happy to.

02:51.250 --> 02:53.855
Hell, I cut and hauled

02:53.910 --> 02:56.162
just under a thousand acres
over to Charley.

02:56.210 --> 03:00.567
Turns out we got some rain
a few days before the harvest,

03:00.610 --> 03:02.566
so mine's was wet and muddy.

03:02.610 --> 03:03.520
[vehicle approaching ]

03:05.270 --> 03:07.613
Is that a problem
for a mill?

03:07.660 --> 03:10.788
Well,
if we ain't ready, sure.

03:10.840 --> 03:14.742
Did Queen Sugar experience
any shutdowns or issues
during your grind?

03:14.800 --> 03:16.222
No, ma'am.

03:16.280 --> 03:18.669
Shoot, Charley did
a great job...

03:18.720 --> 03:20.449
Darla:
Hey, Nova.

03:20.500 --> 03:22.195
I, um...

03:22.240 --> 03:24.583
figured he'd be
out in the fields,
harvesting the cane,

03:24.630 --> 03:27.417
and I could slip in and out
without anybody knowing.

03:29.730 --> 03:31.948
You do a lot of things
without anyone knowing,

03:31.990 --> 03:33.298
don't you?

03:35.470 --> 03:38.075
I don't know.

03:38.130 --> 03:40.382
Look, Nova...

03:40.430 --> 03:42.990
I don't want
any trouble.

03:43.040 --> 03:45.258
I just came to pick up
a few things.

03:45.310 --> 03:48.473
Grab my phone charger
in case Ralph Angel calls me

03:48.530 --> 03:51.135
or if Violet
calls about Blue.

03:53.140 --> 03:55.961
So if you don't mind,
I'll just go grab--

03:56.010 --> 03:59.571
I don't think
you should be
in the house

03:59.630 --> 04:00.574
if Rah isn't here.

04:03.150 --> 04:04.663
This is my home.

04:07.150 --> 04:08.890
I'm raising our son here.

04:08.940 --> 04:11.192
This is ourhome.

04:12.680 --> 04:14.238
And let me be clear--

04:14.290 --> 04:16.429
I don't trust you.

04:20.210 --> 04:22.735
Why didn't you
say something, Darla?

04:22.780 --> 04:25.340
I keep asking myself
that same thing.

04:25.390 --> 04:28.382
Yeah, I can understand
if you were too strung out

04:28.440 --> 04:31.136
to be able to get
yourself together
enough to tell him.

04:31.180 --> 04:33.910
But as soon
as you were sober,

04:33.960 --> 04:37.703
and if you loved him
and wanted to make amends,

04:37.750 --> 04:40.799
ain't you supposed
to share your story?

04:40.840 --> 04:42.967
No matter how hard it is.

04:45.110 --> 04:46.623
I wanted to.

04:48.850 --> 04:50.750
But I was afraid that
he'd walk further away.

04:51.900 --> 04:54.414
He was so angry
at me, Nova.

04:54.460 --> 04:56.189
At everything.

04:57.420 --> 04:58.899
[ sighs ]

04:58.950 --> 05:01.293
But Blue brought him
so much joy.

05:03.210 --> 05:04.689
Real peace.

05:07.350 --> 05:08.681
I just couldn't tell him.

05:08.740 --> 05:10.605
What about Violet?

05:11.740 --> 05:12.957
Hollywood?

05:14.400 --> 05:16.960
After they saved you
and your child?

05:18.400 --> 05:20.265
I did the best I could.

05:22.400 --> 05:25.574
I chose what...

05:25.620 --> 05:27.838
I chose what I thought
would be right for Blue
at all times.

05:27.890 --> 05:29.710
You chose lies.

05:33.850 --> 05:35.545
I think
you should go, Darla.

05:37.590 --> 05:39.455
And come back
when Rah is here
to deal with you.

06:04.400 --> 06:08.313
[ car door opens,
closes ]

06:12.110 --> 06:15.068
[ door opens, closes ]

06:17.550 --> 06:18.972
Miss Bordelon,

06:19.030 --> 06:20.804
I've been expecting you.

06:20.850 --> 06:23.933
There's no way you're expecting
what's about to happen.

06:23.990 --> 06:26.242
You're good at this--

06:26.290 --> 06:29.248
the whole intimidation thing.

06:29.300 --> 06:31.109
I won't lie.

06:31.170 --> 06:35.550
You got me
a couple of times thinking,
"What's she gonna do?"

06:37.300 --> 06:39.655
But in the end,
nothing.

06:39.700 --> 06:41.736
It's all smoke.

06:41.790 --> 06:46.830
If redirecting 50%
of the western farms_
from your mill to my mill

06:46.880 --> 06:49.576
in less_than six months
IS smoke...

06:49.620 --> 06:51.668
I guess I'm the fire.

06:53.230 --> 06:55.846
And I can stay here with you
and trade one-liners

06:55.890 --> 06:57.448
while you look shook
all day,

06:57.500 --> 06:59.752
but we both have
better things to do.

06:59.810 --> 07:03.541
I quite like
trading barbs
with you, Charley.

07:03.590 --> 07:04.636
Gets my blood up.

07:04.680 --> 07:06.409
Sure, it does.

07:06.460 --> 07:07.461
This is a game to you.

07:07.510 --> 07:09.410
You'll resort to threat,

07:09.470 --> 07:14.339
theft, and, hell,
even send a drone to spy.

07:14.390 --> 07:16.950
Sad thing is
none of it's working.

07:17.000 --> 07:19.605
Oh, it's working a little.

07:21.260 --> 07:23.308
That's why you come.

07:23.350 --> 07:25.523
Folks are running
away from you.

07:28.360 --> 07:32.262
- Rumors,
they're wicked things.
- Mm-hmm.

07:32.320 --> 07:33.833
They are.

07:33.880 --> 07:36.485
They're also impermanent.

07:36.540 --> 07:39.145
Fleeting, transient.

07:39.190 --> 07:41.101
Only the truth
stands still.

07:45.760 --> 07:47.842
[ sighs ]

07:52.990 --> 07:55.550
It doesn't have
to be this way.

07:55.600 --> 07:58.854
- I assume your way
is the preferred way.
- It is.

07:58.910 --> 08:02.778
You see, my way,
we don't fight each other.

08:02.830 --> 08:04.479
We fight for each other.

08:04.520 --> 08:06.124
And why on earth
would I want to do that?

08:06.180 --> 08:10.344
Because we could both make
a lot more money that way.

08:10.400 --> 08:12.743
Because your strong mind

08:12.790 --> 08:17.261
and my strong connections
could make us unstoppable.

08:20.360 --> 08:25.104
And _because
I Intrigue you.

08:28.070 --> 08:31.892
And you intoxicate me.

08:34.380 --> 08:35.722
[ scoffs ]

08:40.340 --> 08:42.865
If you're anything, Charley,
you're a pragmatist.

08:42.910 --> 08:45.344
I'm not asking
for unconditional surrender.

08:45.390 --> 08:47.517
I'm willing to negotiate.

08:47.570 --> 08:50.562
We can take it all...

08:50.610 --> 08:52.919
together.

08:52.960 --> 08:56.088
The audacity of privilege.

08:57.400 --> 08:58.617
[ scoffs ]

09:01.620 --> 09:03.053
Jacob...

09:04.710 --> 09:06.758
you're desperate.

09:06.800 --> 09:09.143
You can fuss and fight

09:09.200 --> 09:12.840
and lie and cheat
and flirt all you want.

09:12.900 --> 09:16.199
In the end,
I'll still win.

09:18.640 --> 09:22.633
This is the beginning
of the end for your way
of doing business.

09:22.690 --> 09:26.512
Maybe not next month
or next year,

09:26.560 --> 09:29.643
but the end is coming.

09:32.310 --> 09:35.347
And that ain't
blowing smoke.

09:44.970 --> 09:47.313
[ door opens, closes ]

10:22.180 --> 10:26.093
[ chattering ]

10:26.140 --> 10:28.449
Violet:
He knows
how to fix bikes.

10:28.490 --> 10:29.354
Look at that.

10:49.210 --> 10:52.111
[ screaming ]

10:57.560 --> 10:58.902
So, this way?

10:58.960 --> 11:00.518
Hollywood:
That's-- ah, nope.
Other way.

11:00.570 --> 11:01.696
Yep.

11:04.090 --> 11:05.170
Yeah.

11:05.220 --> 11:06.915
[crying ]

11:10.100 --> 11:12.409
[ cranking ]

11:12.450 --> 11:15.499
- Come-- really tight.
- Uh-huh.

11:28.810 --> 11:30.721
Blue:
Are you done yet, Unc?

11:30.770 --> 11:33.079
Hollywood:
Almost.

11:33.120 --> 11:35.384
- Hollywood: Spin that.
- Violet: Blue.

11:35.430 --> 11:38.422
You know
you got the best hands
working on your bike.

11:38.480 --> 11:40.084
Ido?

11:40.130 --> 11:41.688
You know
how many things

11:41.740 --> 11:43.560
Uncle Hollywood
has fixed for me?

11:45.220 --> 11:47.871
- A lot?
- Violet: A whole lot!

11:47.920 --> 11:50.480
Half the things
in this house would be broke

11:50.530 --> 11:52.043
if it weren't
for those hands.

11:52.100 --> 11:54.796
But I wanna fix them
for you, too, Auntie Vi.

11:54.840 --> 11:56.273
Well...

11:56.320 --> 11:59.665
you know
you got to be smart
to fix things.

11:59.710 --> 12:01.143
And you have
to be strong, too.

12:01.190 --> 12:03.329
I'm strong.

12:03.370 --> 12:05.622
Oh, you are?
Show me.

12:05.680 --> 12:08.240
[ phone ringing ]

12:08.290 --> 12:12.192
Ooh, I gotta feel
those muscles.

12:13.470 --> 12:15.552
Hello?

12:15.600 --> 12:16.942
Yes, it is.

12:19.170 --> 12:22.549
Oh, no, no, no, my full name
is Hollingsworth Desonier.

12:23.830 --> 12:26.037
Let me see.

12:26.090 --> 12:29.867
Yes, the Octa Oleum.

12:29.920 --> 12:31.308
Yeah, I already gave
my deposition.

12:31.350 --> 12:32.908
1--

12:32.960 --> 12:34.393
- Uh-huh.
- [ Violet laughing ]

12:34.440 --> 12:36.522
Blue:
Worked them
pretty good.

12:36.580 --> 12:37.877
I see.

12:39.620 --> 12:42.180
No-- yes, indeed.

12:45.460 --> 12:48.406
Well, thank you.
I...

12:48.460 --> 12:50.496
Thank you very much.

12:53.640 --> 12:54.937
[ beeps ]

12:58.860 --> 13:01.988
[ sighs ]

13:09.960 --> 13:11.040
[ chuckles ]

13:11.090 --> 13:12.990
What you smiling at?

13:13.050 --> 13:14.915
We celebrating, Vi.

13:14.960 --> 13:17.349
We celebrating.
Oh, Vi.

13:17.400 --> 13:19.527
Hollywood,
what on God's good earth?

13:19.580 --> 13:22.617
That was the lavwer
from the rig.

13:22.670 --> 13:24.888
They settled.

13:24.930 --> 13:27.364
Baby, we rich.

13:27.410 --> 13:29.321
Oh, Hollywood,

13:29.370 --> 13:32.271
baby, I know that
that's a nice, tidy sum
of money and all, but--

13:32.330 --> 13:34.457
Uh, uh, uh,
uh, uh, uh.

13:34.500 --> 13:37.503
They settled for triple
of what we thought.

13:39.070 --> 13:40.628
[ mouthing words ]

13:40.680 --> 13:42.159
[ chuckles ]

13:42.210 --> 13:43.552
Are you sure?

13:45.910 --> 13:49.129
You brought me
back to life.

13:49.170 --> 13:51.957
Parthena:
My youngest, Derek,
he's a good soul.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.606
Got mixed up
with the wrong crowd
when he went out West.

13:55.660 --> 13:59.005
It was a second strike
and his wife Ruby had left him.

13:59.050 --> 14:01.610
And it was all on us.

14:01.660 --> 14:06.131
We barely got enough money
together to bail him out
before the trial.

14:06.190 --> 14:09.318
Your sister came through with
some help from her bail fund,

14:09.370 --> 14:11.759
but now we got
legal fees.

14:11.800 --> 14:13.882
Miss Parthena,

14:13.940 --> 14:16.545
if there's something
I could do to help
y'all out...

14:16.590 --> 14:18.364
If Nova needs
to write a story or--

14:18.420 --> 14:21.412
I keep hearing
so much funny business
about Queen Sugar--

14:21.460 --> 14:23.849
See, that's all rumors.
That's all that is.

14:23.900 --> 14:26.368
Rumors usually start
with a seed of truth.

14:26.430 --> 14:28.682
Ain't no truth
to none of it.

14:28.730 --> 14:30.550
Boudreaux and Landrys
just lying.

14:30.600 --> 14:33.865
I can't risk
my son's future
on a maybe.

14:33.910 --> 14:37.994
I came to you
out of respect
for Ernest

14:38.050 --> 14:41.133
and because I know you.

14:41.180 --> 14:44.229
And I don't know
Charley as well.

14:44.270 --> 14:47.649
I was hoping you could
tell her we gotta take
our cane elsewhere.

14:47.710 --> 14:49.746
We?

14:49.800 --> 14:51.927
My brother Bird gonna take
his cane, too.

14:51.970 --> 14:53.972
But just this year.

14:54.020 --> 14:56.272
Ain't gonna be a next year
if we keep going at this rate.

15:00.720 --> 15:03.416
Please, Ralph Angel.

15:03.460 --> 15:06.156
I wouldn't do this
if I knew another way.

15:12.250 --> 15:14.070
I'll deal with Charley.

15:16.740 --> 15:18.423
Bless you.

15:18.480 --> 15:20.345
[vehicle approaching ]

15:36.410 --> 15:38.924
No, no, no, everything
is working fine here--

15:40.020 --> 15:41.237
[ phone beeps ]

15:45.850 --> 15:49.240
You can come
and see for yourself.

15:49.290 --> 15:50.678
Better yet,
you know what?

15:50.730 --> 15:52.243
Why don't you give
Mr. Duvall a call?

15:52.290 --> 15:55.555
He-- he's already
milled with us--

15:55.600 --> 15:57.386
[ sighs ]

15:57.430 --> 15:58.818
[ phone beeps ]

16:01.910 --> 16:04.515
No, all of the machinery
is working.

16:04.570 --> 16:06.959
You-- you don't
have to do this!

16:08.440 --> 16:11.227
- [ sighs ] Yeah.
- [ phone beeps ]

16:11.270 --> 16:13.488
- They're taking 40%--
- [ dial tone humming ]

16:13.530 --> 16:16.795
You know, there is a penalty
for breaking your contract.

16:16.840 --> 16:19.183
And you don't care.

16:21.800 --> 16:24.268
[ chatter ]

16:47.040 --> 16:48.917
Violet:
This what it feels like
to be rich?

16:48.960 --> 16:51.474
Hollywood:
Mm-hmm.

16:51.530 --> 16:54.693
I don't feel no different,
at least not yet.

16:56.140 --> 16:58.392
You know why?

16:58.450 --> 17:00.270
'Cause we've been rich
for years.

17:00.320 --> 17:03.619
Hmm, then why have
I been sweating away

17:03.670 --> 17:05.752
at the High Yellow
all this time?

17:05.800 --> 17:07.711
Ah, no,
hear me, now.

17:07.760 --> 17:12.584
We rich in love,
in each other.

17:12.640 --> 17:15.803
Eh, money ain't
gonna do nothing
but make that better.

17:15.860 --> 17:18.078
I don't know, Hollywood.

17:18.120 --> 17:21.078
What about all those
Super Lotto folks?

17:21.120 --> 17:23.509
Baml
They got money

17:28.350 --> 17:30.602
suing each other
for some foolishness.

17:30.650 --> 17:34.040
Stop worrying
and dream, woman.

17:34.090 --> 17:36.877
Dream.

17:36.920 --> 17:39.525
I hear you.

17:39.580 --> 17:41.969
I'm gonna take my time
with that.

17:45.020 --> 17:46.271
Good.

17:49.850 --> 17:51.841
But I don't need
to take no time.

17:53.720 --> 17:55.676
I know what I want.

17:55.720 --> 17:58.188
What's that?

17:58.250 --> 18:01.799
You... forever.

18:05.300 --> 18:07.291
For real.

18:07.340 --> 18:08.728
On paper.

18:13.000 --> 18:17.562
I know we said
we never needed that...

18:17.610 --> 18:19.919
but I want it now.

18:19.960 --> 18:23.043
Oh, Hollywood.

18:23.100 --> 18:24.909
Think on what
you're saying, baby.

18:24.970 --> 18:26.449
I don't need to.

18:28.890 --> 18:32.621
Violet, so many people
out here alone,

18:32.670 --> 18:35.104
wishing they had
half of what we got.

18:37.980 --> 18:42.110
Woman, I ain't
never had nothing
like you in my life.

18:48.770 --> 18:50.556
I feel the same.

18:57.830 --> 18:59.650
Let's lock this down,
chre.

19:06.490 --> 19:07.832
Violet...

19:10.620 --> 19:16.104
would you consider
marrying me?

19:33.910 --> 19:35.719
Yes, baby.

19:36.950 --> 19:39.737
Yes, yes, yes.

19:44.050 --> 19:47.611
Oh, a hundred times yes.

19:47.660 --> 19:49.173
[ sighs ]

19:59.580 --> 20:01.628
[ knocking ]

20:05.200 --> 20:07.020
- Hi.
- Hey, baby.

20:07.070 --> 20:09.243
- Nova: How you doing, Blue?
- Blue: Hi, Auntie Nova.

20:09.290 --> 20:11.542
[ giggling ]

20:11.600 --> 20:13.409
Welcome to your
engagement dinner.

20:13.470 --> 20:16.985
Oh, I can't believe you
with all this.

20:17.040 --> 20:18.519
Believe it.

20:18.560 --> 20:20.869
Between the harvest
and the mill drama,

20:20.910 --> 20:25.995
this can't and will not
fall through the cracks.

20:26.050 --> 20:28.120
This, this right here...

20:29.440 --> 20:30.657
this is precious.

20:30.700 --> 20:33.521
And worthy
of a celebration!

20:33.580 --> 20:37.129
- Let the church say...
- Amen!

20:37.190 --> 20:38.748
Charley and Remy
are on their way.

20:38.800 --> 20:40.495
Rah, Micah, and Prosper
are still working,

20:40.540 --> 20:43.008
but I couldn't wait.

20:43.060 --> 20:45.016
I couldn't
let this day pass

20:45.060 --> 20:48.234
without marking
its significance.

20:48.290 --> 20:52.067
Not just for you two,

20:52.120 --> 20:53.599
