45:18.010 --> 45:19.318
Look”.

45:20.840 --> 45:23.718
I know I ain't always
done right by it.

45:25.330 --> 45:28.891
A lot of times I ain't
say the right thing

45:28.940 --> 45:31.841
or do the right thing.

45:34.420 --> 45:36.285
I got a past.

45:37.900 --> 45:39.595
I got a temper.

45:40.910 --> 45:44.380
I got baggage,
I admit it.

45:45.960 --> 45:47.564
But with all of that...

45:49.480 --> 45:51.436
I can
honest to God say...

45:53.480 --> 45:55.482
I never lied to you.

45:57.710 --> 46:00.611
Of all the things
I thought you was,

46:00.670 --> 46:03.309
a liar was never
one of them.

46:05.710 --> 46:07.109
Maybe...

46:10.070 --> 46:13.028
Maybe you'll see
things differently
if you hear me out.

46:15.640 --> 46:17.028
I'm listening.

46:17.070 --> 46:19.152
I was home
for the weekend.

46:19.210 --> 46:21.337
In DC.

46:24.040 --> 46:25.519
And I was using.

46:27.430 --> 46:31.082
And there was a party
with some boys--

46:31.130 --> 46:33.178
I ain't trying to hear about
who you did what with.

46:36.660 --> 46:39.788
Iwanna know _
why you carried a lie

46:39.840 --> 46:41.444
for the last seven years.

46:44.140 --> 46:47.359
Why you looked me
in my face

46:47.410 --> 46:49.014
and told me
you loved me?

46:49.060 --> 46:51.620
- Because I do.
- And told me you was clean

46:51.670 --> 46:54.230
and sober
and working your steps.

46:54.280 --> 46:58.319
You told me that
all that matters to you
is me and Blue.

46:58.380 --> 47:03.022
- All that is true.
- Then you turn around
and keep a lie like this?

47:04.730 --> 47:07.244
A poison like this?

47:09.910 --> 47:12.037
I wanna know why.

47:17.260 --> 47:20.263
There's no excuse.
Wsumm

47:24.270 --> 47:25.874
It's unacceptable.

47:25.930 --> 47:27.704
But here you are...

47:29.280 --> 47:31.054
asking me to accept it.

47:31.100 --> 47:32.795
I'm asking you
to try and understand.

47:32.850 --> 47:36.229
So tell me something
I need to understand!

47:36.280 --> 47:38.840
You talking,

47:38.890 --> 47:40.846
but you ain't saying nothing
that mean nothing yet.

47:40.900 --> 47:43.585
I was scared!

47:43.640 --> 47:46.541
I was scared
for my life, okay?

47:52.040 --> 47:55.680
That I couldn't remember
what happened with those guys.

47:59.390 --> 48:02.348
That I ended up pregnant.

48:02.400 --> 48:06.962
And I didn't know
if it happened that night

48:07.010 --> 48:09.649
or with the man
that I was in love with.

48:13.620 --> 48:17.533
That if I had a baby,
I couldn't use.

48:26.380 --> 48:27.859
[ sighs ]

48:27.900 --> 48:29.800
Then you get locked up.

48:33.210 --> 48:34.939
And everything
fell apart.

48:34.990 --> 48:37.948
[ sniffles, sighs ]

48:42.180 --> 48:44.250
What was I supposed
to say?

48:48.400 --> 48:50.709
What was I supposed
to say to you?

48:51.840 --> 48:55.879
You say, "I'm pregnant.

48:57.320 --> 49:00.278
And I don't know
if it's yours."

49:01.670 --> 49:04.719
Just like that,
from the jump.

49:08.240 --> 49:10.765
I remember the day
you told me.

49:13.770 --> 49:16.989
Been over it again
and again in my head.

49:19.860 --> 49:25.082
You told me
that he was mine.

49:27.570 --> 49:29.561
You let me celebrate.

49:31.920 --> 49:33.524
You let me be proud.

49:37.060 --> 49:40.575
And then you took--
took it all away from me.

49:42.890 --> 49:45.586
After all
my family did.

49:47.500 --> 49:50.287
[ crying ]
You ain't have
to do it this way.

49:52.770 --> 49:54.067
I wanted it to be true.

49:54.120 --> 49:57.021
It ain't true!

49:57.080 --> 50:00.982
You lied that day
and every goddamned day since.

50:01.040 --> 50:03.122
You...

50:03.170 --> 50:07.288
you lied about it all.

50:11.350 --> 50:13.568
Blue...

50:13.610 --> 50:16.135
Darla, come on.

50:16.180 --> 50:17.738
How could you?

50:20.660 --> 50:22.571
I betrayed you.

50:26.630 --> 50:31.067
And I deserve
whatever you decide.

50:35.240 --> 50:37.196
But I need you
to know...

50:40.250 --> 50:43.299
that every part
of me...

50:45.910 --> 50:47.901
I am so sorry.

50:53.740 --> 50:56.265
And I hope someday
you can forgive me.

51:03.400 --> 51:06.528
I'll never look at you
the same.

51:09.890 --> 51:12.882
I'll never _
trust you again.

51:39.440 --> 51:41.214
We're over?

51:42.660 --> 51:44.389
I can't.

51:46.970 --> 51:49.530
How I'm gonna be
with you if I--

51:49.580 --> 51:51.184
if I can't trust you?

51:53.280 --> 51:55.532
I-- I can't do it.

51:55.590 --> 51:57.273
What about Blue?

52:02.680 --> 52:04.728
You can leave me...

52:06.860 --> 52:08.634
you can turn away
from me...

52:11.250 --> 52:13.639
but please don't
turn away from Blue.

52:15.870 --> 52:20.694
Hate me, but not him.

52:20.740 --> 52:24.005
He loves you so much,
Ralph Angel.

52:26.790 --> 52:28.610
Please love Blue.

52:38.760 --> 52:41.490
Blue is the_ blood
in my veins...

52:44.770 --> 52:47.113
even if mine
ain't in his.

52:56.120 --> 52:58.202
You'll take him
for a while?

53:00.740 --> 53:02.128
I got him.

53:09.270 --> 53:10.999
So what you gonna do?

53:13.010 --> 53:17.049
I'll go home
to my parents and...

53:18.710 --> 53:20.018
try to--

53:26.630 --> 53:28.495
try to continue.

53:32.470 --> 53:34.199
Tell him, um...

53:37.080 --> 53:39.810
Tell him I got
a little sick.

53:39.860 --> 53:41.464
And, um...

53:42.870 --> 53:44.644
I went to get better.

53:48.920 --> 53:51.605
And that I'll be back
to take him swimming.

54:00.140 --> 54:02.142
God bless you, Darla.

54:04.370 --> 54:05.928
I mean that.

54:05.980 --> 54:07.845
[crying ]

54:43.060 --> 54:45.528
Jacob:
I didn't expect
to see you for a while.

54:45.580 --> 54:47.628
That makes two of us.

54:47.670 --> 54:50.230
What changed?

54:50.280 --> 54:55.320
I want to apologize
for being abrupt

54:55.370 --> 54:56.928
the other day.

54:56.980 --> 54:58.322
You were trying
to make an offer

54:58.380 --> 55:00.940
and I was
caught up in...

55:02.730 --> 55:03.594
ego.

55:05.560 --> 55:07.596
My eyes are open now.

55:09.210 --> 55:10.859
Tell me what you want.

55:12.870 --> 55:15.304
You.

55:15.350 --> 55:18.399
The mill is just
a place to begin.

55:18.440 --> 55:19.998
You and me,

55:20.050 --> 55:24.612
we could make
a_ formidable team
in this busmess,

55:24.660 --> 55:28.573
especially if people
don't know we're a team.

55:30.100 --> 55:32.056
Partner with me.

55:32.110 --> 55:34.499
Let's take everything
up a notch.

55:35.630 --> 55:38.019
No partnership.

55:38.070 --> 55:40.106
You're buying it outright.

55:40.160 --> 55:42.981
[ chuckles ]

55:43.030 --> 55:44.895
You fought
all these months

55:44.950 --> 55:47.077
to get your mill
up and running,

55:47.120 --> 55:50.908
stole our farmers away,
and now you want to sell?

55:52.170 --> 55:55.424
I'm tired of fighting.

55:57.700 --> 56:00.089
Truth is,
I've lost a lot.

56:03.050 --> 56:05.746
I was so focused
on Winning...

56:08.100 --> 56:10.261
I wasn't there
for my son,

56:10.320 --> 56:15.189
I alienated
my whole family,

56:15.240 --> 56:16.582
and, um...

56:16.630 --> 56:21.101
it cost me a very...

56:26.160 --> 56:30.119
important relationship.

56:36.480 --> 56:40.439
My daddy,
he used to say,

56:40.480 --> 56:43.608
"If you set after
doing something

56:43.660 --> 56:47.619
and learn a lesson
on the way...

56:51.490 --> 56:53.264
even if you lose...

56:55.360 --> 56:56.884
it's still a victory."

56:59.800 --> 57:02.883
Selling the mill is far

57:02.940 --> 57:06.103
from the hopes and dreams
I had when I had bought it.

57:10.250 --> 57:12.286
But I find that...

57:13.950 --> 57:16.032
dreams are funny things.

57:18.040 --> 57:20.679
They, uh--
they morph...

57:24.040 --> 57:25.473
and reshape...

57:27.260 --> 57:28.955
in an instant.

57:36.540 --> 57:38.223
So here's the deal.

57:41.500 --> 57:44.401
I continue to oversee
the day-to-day operations,

57:44.460 --> 57:46.587
salaried.

57:46.630 --> 57:49.497
I remain the face
and driving force.

57:53.120 --> 57:54.337
and they'll mill
with me.

57:55.770 --> 57:59.809
And you and I arrange
a refinery percentage.

58:01.820 --> 58:03.469
And equity.

58:07.040 --> 58:11.522
Now how about
another arrangement?

58:22.280 --> 58:25.317
One step at a time,

58:25.370 --> 58:26.712
Mr. Boudreaux.

58:32.940 --> 58:35.454
Yes, ma'am,

58:35.510 --> 58:37.159
Miss Bordelon.

58:42.990 --> 58:44.685
You have a deal.

58:48.220 --> 58:49.164
[ glasses clink]

58:49.220 --> 58:51.211
[ chuckles ]

59:05.410 --> 59:07.753
- Y'all drive safe_now.
- AppreCIate it.

59:07.800 --> 59:11.054
- Love you.
- Love you, too.

59:11.110 --> 59:13.544
- Y'all have a good night.
- Hollywood: All right.

59:27.730 --> 59:31.166
- Ididn't know
I was looking for you...
- All right, come on.

59:31.210 --> 59:34.509
I didn't know there was
something to find...

59:34.570 --> 59:36.470
I got you.

59:36.520 --> 59:40.308
Tomorrow you won't fit
in yesterday's shoes

59:40.350 --> 59:44.389
I'm trying so hard
to rewind...

59:44.450 --> 59:47.010
[ seatbelt clicking ]

59:49.280 --> 59:50.793
Hi, Pop.

59:53.450 --> 59:54.621
Hi, Blue.

59:54.670 --> 59:57.138
Where have you been?

59:58.420 --> 1:00:00.320
It's harvest time,
remember?

1:00:03.460 --> 1:00:06.463
Oh. Yeah.

1:00:07.690 --> 1:00:09.851
Figured you'd be here

1:00:09.910 --> 1:00:13.641
with Aunt Vi,
good fun, good food.

1:00:13.690 --> 1:00:16.955
Now I'm bringing in
the harvest.

1:00:17.000 --> 1:00:18.865
Okay.

1:00:18.910 --> 1:00:21.913
Forever I'll _follow
your trail...

1:00:21.960 --> 1:00:23.871
Where do you think
I was, Blue?

1:00:26.750 --> 1:00:28.399
I don't know.

1:00:40.680 --> 1:00:42.932
I never told you
how you got your name, did I?

1:00:45.380 --> 1:00:48.679
Well, at first,

1:00:48.730 --> 1:00:51.153
I wanted to name you
Andrew or Brian.

1:00:52.950 --> 1:00:57.125
Thought those were names
of good people everybody liked.

1:00:57.170 --> 1:00:59.900
You know,
stayed out of trouble.

1:01:01.740 --> 1:01:03.344
Them solid people.

1:01:05.440 --> 1:01:08.000
But your mama wanted
to name you Troy or Cornell.

1:01:09.360 --> 1:01:12.227
- Cornell?
- Yeah, Cornell.

1:01:12.270 --> 1:01:15.273
Cornell Bordelon,
that was about to be you.

1:01:18.190 --> 1:01:20.658
Papa wanted
to name you Percy.

1:01:20.720 --> 1:01:22.403
[ scoffs ]

1:01:22.460 --> 1:01:27.363
He had a cousin named Percy,
said he was a good man.

1:01:27.420 --> 1:01:31.413
And so he wanted
to honor him with the name,

1:01:31.470 --> 1:01:33.688
you know, keep it
in the family.

1:01:36.600 --> 1:01:40.070
But I wanted you
to have your own name.

1:01:40.130 --> 1:01:43.429
Something that nobody
in the family ever had before.

1:01:44.780 --> 1:01:48.341
And I started thinking...

1:01:48.400 --> 1:01:51.915
I should give you
a rare name.

1:01:51.960 --> 1:01:55.316
Something that
not a lot of people have
in the whole wide world.

1:01:56.930 --> 1:01:59.057
So dig this.

1:01:59.100 --> 1:02:01.625
I'm in the kitchen
with Aunt Vi, right?

1:02:01.670 --> 1:02:03.183
She cooking up
her smothered chicken.

1:02:03.240 --> 1:02:06.494
- [ both chuckle ]
- You know you like that.

1:02:06.540 --> 1:02:09.327
And we talking about
what I'm gonna name you.

1:02:09.370 --> 1:02:11.452
Tells me a story

1:02:11.510 --> 1:02:15.150
about the first time
she realized her name
was a color.

1:02:16.290 --> 1:02:18.019
A little girl

1:02:18.080 --> 1:02:21.379
saw her name
on a crayon
at school.

1:02:23.650 --> 1:02:25.777
Said that she felt special
her name could make

1:02:25.820 --> 1:02:27.082
something so pretty--

1:02:27.130 --> 1:02:29.303
the color violet.

1:02:31.090 --> 1:02:33.081
So I thought
about that.

1:02:34.790 --> 1:02:39.352
And there was one
that was... perfect.

1:02:41.400 --> 1:02:43.402
Just like the color violet.

1:02:45.280 --> 1:02:47.919
And it rhymes
with my mama's name...

1:02:50.330 --> 1:02:51.752
True.

1:02:54.110 --> 1:02:57.500
I could name you...

1:02:57.550 --> 1:03:00.155
after the two ladies
in my life

1:03:00.210 --> 1:03:02.599
who always
believed in me...

1:03:04.170 --> 1:03:05.819
no matter what.

1:03:07.520 --> 1:03:09.647
Just like
I'll believe in you...

1:03:10.960 --> 1:03:12.382
no matter what.

1:03:14.130 --> 1:03:16.212
Blue was them.

1:03:17.570 --> 1:03:21.870
Blue was the sky,
blue was the ocean.

1:03:23.140 --> 1:03:24.789
It's everything good.

1:03:26.970 --> 1:03:28.449
That's you, son.

1:03:30.320 --> 1:03:31.799
Everything good.

1:03:33.200 --> 1:03:34.326
You got it?

1:03:34.370 --> 1:03:36.895
Got it, Pop.

1:03:46.510 --> 1:03:48.296
I love you, son.

1:03:58.920 --> 1:04:01.309
[ seatbelt clicks ]

1:04:08.190 --> 1:04:10.750
[ door opens, closes ]

1:04:14.110 --> 1:04:15.839
[ engine starts ]

1:04:26.380 --> 1:04:30.373
May all your prayers
be answered

1:04:39.310 --> 1:04:43.735
May all your prayers
be answered.
